ext-decoration: underline;">The maze is in the mouse</a></em><span> (which =
you should read if you want to viscerally feel how heavy being Positioned c=
an be), ex-Googler (Xoogler?) Praveen Seshadri wrote:&nbsp;</span></p><bloc=
kquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;=
"><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>While two of Google&#8217;s core v=
alues are &#8220;respect the user&#8221; and &#8220;respect the opportunity=
&#8221;, </span><strong>in practice the systems and processes are intention=
ally designed to &#8220;respect risk&#8221;. Risk mitigation trumps everyth=
ing else.</strong><span> This makes sense if everything is going wonderfull=
y and the most important thing is to avoid rocking the boat and keep sailin=
g on the rising tide of ads revenue. In such a world, potential risk lies e=
verywhere you look. People act accordingly:</span></em></p></blockquote><ul=
 style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; ms=
o-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #4040=
40; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; paddin=
g-left: 4px;"><em>every line of code you change is risk, so put in a ton of=
 processes to ensure that that every code change is perfect at avoiding ris=
k (never mind if it is uninspiring for the user)</em></p></li><li style=3D"=
margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: =
border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; =
margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><em>anything you launch is risk, so p=
ut in a ton of reviews and approvals (literally 15+ approvals in a &#8220;l=
aunch&#8221; process that mirrors the complexity of a Nasa space launch) ju=
st to deploy each minor change to a minor product</em></p></li><li style=3D=
"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing:=
 border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;=
 margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><em>any non-obvious decision is risk=
, so avoid anything that isn&#8217;t group think and conventional wisdom</e=
m></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;">=
<p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><em>any chang=
e from the way things used to be done is risk, so stick to how it was&#8230=
;</em></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This isn&#8217;t the Innovator&#8217;s Dilemm=
