 font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 =
0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>Organizing the World&#8217;s Inform=
ation</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Google is facing an existential threat, if not=
 an Innovator&#8217;s Dilemma. Through its entire history, it&#8217;s built=
 skills and structures that reinforce its ability to give the best links fo=
r any given search query, and to sell ads against those searches. It has be=
come deeply, deeply positioned in search.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #4040=
40; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Now that AI&#8=
217;s time has finally come and the battleground is shifting rapidly, Googl=
e&#8217;s strengths have become weaknesses. It has a lot to lose, and risks=
 losing it all by not taking risks. To survive, it will need to cut weight,=
 take risks, and move fast.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Just as Microsoft under Nade=
lla shifted from a Windows company to an enterprise productivity company, f=
rom a Product to a Platform, Google needs to return to its mission and shif=
t from a search company to an information organization company.&nbsp;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 2=
0px 0;"><span>Efforts are underway in Mountain View to build AI into everyt=
hing that Google does. Larry and Sergey have come back to work on AI. Googl=
e launched </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/30b364be-dbd1-45=
24-b25b-0f4eb44b855d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;=
">Bard</a><span>, its somewhat weaker ChatGPT competitor. It&#8217;s put to=
gether a 160 person team to work on Project Magi, its efforts to infuse AI =
into its search product.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The good news about bein=
g Positioned is that it&#8217;s actually somewhat easier to deal with than =
the Innovator&#8217;s Dilemma once a company acknowledges that it&#8217;s n=
o longer in a war of position but a war of maneuver. The Innovator&#8217;s =
Dilemma requires companies to take a bet on external factors &#8211; whethe=
r or not there will be a market for this crappy new thing eventually &#8211=
; but in the case of AI, there&#8217;s no doubt about the size of the prize=
 for the winners. The required shift is an internal one, a coming-to-grips =
with the fact that what got you here won&#8217;t get you there.&nbsp;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 2=
0px 0;">Luckily, the Position that Google has built up over the past 25 yea=
rs gives it a lot of the pieces required to thrive.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><spa=
n>Google.com is the most trafficked website in the world. When </span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/35ec34fc-ac4c-49bd-bbd2-ea7ffbb684a2?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D""=
 style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Attention is All You=
 Need</a><span>, that&#8217;s an invaluable asset. While ChatGPT and Bing h=
ave garnered the early attention, if Google moves relatively quickly, it wi=
ll provide most people&#8217;s first interaction with LLM-based products.</=
span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;">Just as that volume gives Google the ability to provide =
better search results for the new things people search every day, it might =
also give Google&#8217;s LLMs the ability to learn more quickly. It&#8217;s=
 a captive data source in a world in which captive data sources matter more=
 than ever.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As models become more multi-modal, and as vi=
deo becomes a bigger part of the AI story, Google&#8217;s treasure trove of=
 YouTube videos will be an invaluable resource.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>De=
spite losing the authors of the Transformer paper, </span><a href=3D"https:=
//substack.com/redirect/677b28cd-d527-4bef-9d8c-bc6500ee3424?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"col=
or: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Google Brain DeepMind</a><span> i=
s still one of the most formidable AI research organizations in the world.&=
nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Through its advertising business, Google has more=
 relationships with companies trying to sell products and services than any=
 other company in the world. If it can shift to become a Platform &#8211; a=
 big shift, to be sure &#8211; it has the potential to build a strong compe=
titor to the ChatGPT plugins ecosystem while that ecosystem is still in its=
 infancy.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As I wrote, I believe that an Apex Aggregator =
that takes actions and makes purchases on its users&#8217; behalf has the c=
hance to become a bigger business than search. No company in the world has =
proven better at monetizing intent than Google has.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><spa=
n>Doing search well is a very hard problem, and no one does it better than =
Google. If it can get its juice back, it can leverage these powerful new AI=
 capabilities to build products that organize the world&#8217;s information=
 and make it accessible and useful, even if that sometimes means putting se=
arch </span><em>ads</em><span> second.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #=
404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Of course,=
 Google has a lot of cultural baggage to shed. It may need to suffer from s=
hort-term revenue hits. It will need to learn to take big risks again. But =
not taking those risks is an even bigger risk: if Google isn&#8217;t willin=
g to cannibalize itself, others will happily eat it.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The=
 things that got Google here as it became more deeply Positioned in search =
during the war of position have become weights in the war of maneuver. But =
they can also be weapons.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px;"><hr style=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 3=
2px 0; padding: 0;"></div><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>Thanks to Dan for editing!</em><spa=
n> </span></p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=
=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding=
: 0;"></div><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That&#8217;s all for today! We&#8217;ll be back in yo=
ur inbox on Friday with a Weekly Dose of Optimism.</p><p style=3D"color: #4=
04040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Thanks for =
reading, </p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Packy</p></div></div><table role=
